Earlier on in December 2019, some of my dad's Christian friends strongly encouraged them to attend church services, in particularly the Christmas celebrations. My parents weren't suspicious but they did gave our home address to the group. From what I heard, it wasn't an official church building but more like an office room in a huge building with all other businesses running and all. There were worse things to come. Since they knew our address, they came and harassed my mother. Firstly, they came to our house, despite my protests, baptized (or what Christians call purification) my parents and call for "God" 's blessings. Secondly, after that day, whenever they came, they brought more people with them and stayed longer outside our door, eventually demanded my mother to give out Christian brochures for them. When my mother claimed that she's not Christian and not willing to be any part of them anymore(only my father is willing to do anything to get free stuff they give out during services or sessions, whatever), they shouted and claimed that my mother "looked down on them". It has been many months since then, but even till now, in this Virus situation, those same Christian friends(who proclaimed to us they are not Christians) are still asking(or more like pleading) my father to go for their whatever church services. We are Buddhists, not Christians. I do not know if it's online or offline, but I do not agree that a religion should demand anyone to belong to them. Keyword, belong. Can I just ask, if people do not want us to spread and preach our religion, forcing people to listen to and obey us, isn't it fair that they do not do so to us too?
